      <hedline>
        <hl1>National Primary Needed</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Andrea B Hale letter says current presidential nomination system is absurd; calls for national primary (Jan 25 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Big States Push for Earlier Vote Scrambles Race'' (front page, Jan. 25):</p>
        <p>Watching the states scramble to set new primary dates just reinforces how absurd the current system is.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Big States Push for Earlier Vote Scrambles Race'' (front page, Jan. 25):</p>
        <p>Watching the states scramble to set new primary dates just reinforces how absurd the current system is.</p>
        <p>Rather than placing the choice of the party nominees in the hands of a few select states, we should institute a national primary day that would allow the citizens of all 50 states to have a voice in the selection process.</p>
        <p>Andrea B. Hale  New York, Jan. 25, 2007</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
